Мопед не мой, но может кто-то захочет завести :petr:

Data Engineer at Yousician

Finland, Helsinki

Salary: 3500 - 4600 EUR monthly

Direct contact: <mailto:magnus@yousician.com|magnus@yousician.com>


<https://boards.greenhouse.io/yousician/jobs/4032479002>

*JOIN YOUSICIAN*
At Yousician, our job is to reimagine music education, so everyone can play. We’ve built an amazing team of creative, passionate, and independent people, all working together to help millions of musicians learn, play, reach their goals, and have fun. If this sounds like the right mission for you, you’re in the right place!

*WHY YOU SHOULD APPLY*
As a Data Engineer, you will be building and maintaining a scalable data pipeline and providing the tools for the teams that facilitate data-driven decision making. You will be involved in all aspects of data analysis, designing and implementing our data architecture and the algorithms that drive our product.

*WHAT YOU’LL DO*
Develop and maintain our data pipeline.
Improve the scaling, optimization, tests and our internal tools to enhance data quality & reliability.
Work with diverse data processing frameworks and technologies and bring new ideas to the table.
Help the team in all aspects of data analysis but with focus on data engineering.
*WHO YOU ARE*
You have experience of building or maintaining a data warehouse or ETL pipeline.
You have hands-on experience with data warehousing technologies (e.g. Redshift, Hadoop, Druid).
You have good experience with TDD in Python and SQL languages.
You have a strong interest in learning/discovering new big data technologies.
You have some linux administration system knowledge.
Experience with AWS and Google Cloud Platform.
Experience with developing complex ETL workflow (Airflow).
*WHAT WE OFFER*
You’ll have a meaningful and profound impact on the lives of millions of musicians and future musicians all around the world.
You’ll get a competitive compensation package - salary, stock options, crazy perks - and work in an awesome new office in the heart of Helsinki.
We have lots of perks and quirks: daily push-up sessions, bonus for sport activities, jam sessions (with more instruments than you can shake a drumstick at!), board game tournaments and sauna evenings, and our famous Greece, Thailand, Tenerife and Bali work-retreats.
*HOW TO APPLY*
Send us your application and CV (in English). Let’s make the world a more musical place together! Everyone who comes to a personal interview at our office gets an ukulele. #rockon
